# Run Tests Guide

This rule explains how to use the `scripts/run_tests.sh` script for running tests in this project to verify and validate failures as soon as possible.

## Default Operation

The recommended way to run tests in this project is:

```bash
./scripts/run_tests.sh --warnings-summary tests/interval_new
```

This runs the new interval tests with Warnings Summary mode, which stops on the first test failure and provides a clear error summary.

## Basic Usage

You can run tests using the following command pattern:

```bash
./scripts/run_tests.sh [test_path] [log_level] [additional_pytest_args]
```

- `test_path`: Optional path to a specific test file or directory (default: tests/)
- `log_level`: Optional log level (DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR) (default: INFO)
- `additional_pytest_args`: Optional additional pytest arguments
